# Database Schema and Migrations

This directory contains the Alembic migrations for the Story Architect Backend.

## Entity-Relationship Diagram

Below is the database schema used by the application:

```mermaid
erDiagram
    Story ||--o{ Character : "has"
    Story ||--o{ Relationship : "has"
    Story ||--o{ DiscoveryEvent : "has"
    
    Character ||--o{ Relationship : "character_a"
    Character ||--o{ Relationship : "character_b"
    Character ||--o| CharacterArchitectureReport : "has"
    Character ||--o{ DiscoveryAnswer : "has"
    Character ||--o{ DiscoveryEvent : "triggers"
    
    Relationship ||--o| RelationshipArchitectureReport : "has"
    Relationship ||--o{ DiscoveryAnswer : "has"
    Relationship ||--o{ DiscoveryEvent : "triggers"
    
    DiscoveryQuestion ||--o{ DiscoveryAnswer : "answered_by"
    
    Story {
        UUID id PK
        string title
        string genre
        string one_sentence_premise
    }
    
    Character {
        UUID id PK
        UUID story_id FK
        string name
        string role
        string archetype
    }
    
    Relationship {
        UUID id PK
        UUID story_id FK
        UUID character_a_id FK
        UUID character_b_id FK
        string relationship_type
        string dynamic
    }
    
    DiscoveryQuestion {
        UUID id PK
        string flow_type
        string question_key
        string question_text
        string array suggested_answers
    }
    
    DiscoveryAnswer {
        UUID id PK
        UUID question_id FK
        UUID story_id FK
        UUID character_id FK
        UUID relationship_id FK
        string answer_text
    }
    
    DiscoveryEvent {
        UUID id PK
        UUID story_id FK
        UUID character_id FK
        UUID relationship_id FK
        string event_type
        string title
        string description
    }
    
    CharacterArchitectureReport {
        UUID id PK
        UUID character_id FK
        string character_core
        string emotional_wound
        string deepest_fear
        string protective_lie
        string relationship_pattern
        string conflict_created
        string transformation
        string narrative_consequence
    }
    
    RelationshipArchitectureReport {
        UUID id PK
        UUID relationship_id FK
        string core_dynamic
        string shared_conflict
    }
```

## Running Migrations

To upgrade the database to the latest schema:
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

To create a new migration after modifying `app/models/`:
```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description of changes"
```

